CHAPTER 3 \'96 REQUIREMENTS AND ANALYSIS\
3.1 Problem Definition\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Developers and students regularly encounter technical problems that require quick, reliable solutions. Existing platforms either lack depth of technical content, have poor search capabilities, or do not incentivise quality contributions. The primary problem addressed by Bug Overflow is the need for an integrated, community-driven Q&A platform that:\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \'95 Provides a structured way to post and answer technical questions.\u8232 \'95 Rewards high-quality contributors through a reputation and badge system.\u8232 \'95 Supports rich-text formatting for code-heavy technical content.\u8232 \'95 Enables article publishing for longer, tutorial-style content.\u8232 \'95 Sends real-time notifications for user interactions.\u8232 \'95 Maintains user bookmarks for frequently referenced content.\u8232 \'95 Implements robust security through JWT authentication and rate limiting.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 3.2 Requirements Specification\
Functional Requirements\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 FR-01: Users shall be able to register with email, username, and password.\
FR-02: Users shall be able to log in and receive JWT access and refresh tokens.\
FR-03: Authenticated users shall be able to post questions with a title, body, and tags.\
FR-04: Authenticated users shall be able to submit answers to any question.\
FR-05: Users shall be able to upvote or downvote questions and answers.\
FR-06: The question owner shall be able to accept one answer as the correct solution.\
FR-07: Users shall be able to post comments on questions and answers.\
FR-08: Users shall be able to search questions by keyword or tag.\
FR-09: Reputation shall be updated automatically on vote and accept events.\
FR-10: Badges shall be awarded automatically when reputation thresholds are reached.\
FR-11: Users shall receive notifications for votes, answers, and comments on their content.\
FR-12: Users shall be able to bookmark questions for later reference.\
FR-13: Users shall be able to write and publish technical articles.\
FR-14: Users shall be able to edit their profile including avatar and bio.\
FR-15: The system shall send password reset emails via Nodemailer.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Non-Functional Requirements\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 NFR-01 \'96 Performance: API responses shall complete within 500ms under normal load.\
NFR-02 \'96 Security: Passwords shall be hashed using bcrypt; tokens stored in HTTP-only cookies.\
NFR-03 \'96 Rate Limiting: API endpoints shall be rate-limited to 100 requests per 15 minutes.\
NFR-04 \'96 Scalability: The MongoDB schema shall support horizontal scaling via sharding.\
NFR-05 \'96 Usability: The UI shall be responsive and accessible on desktop and mobile browsers.\
NFR-06 \'96 Reliability: The system shall handle invalid input gracefully with appropriate error messages.\
NFR-07 \'96 Maintainability: Code shall follow ES module standards with clear separation of concerns.\
NFR-08 \'96 Availability: The application shall be deployable to cloud platforms (Render, Vercel).\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

