\fs24 \cf0 4.3 Use Case Diagram\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The following use case diagram shows the interactions between actors (Guest, Registered User, Admin) and the Bug Overflow system:\uc0\u8232 \u8232 ACTORS:\u8232 \'95 Guest User \'96 Can browse questions, read answers, view profiles, search.\u8232 \'95 Registered User \'96 Can do everything a guest can + post, vote, comment, bookmark, receive notifications.\u8232 \'95 Admin \'96 Can moderate content, manage tags, and access administrative dashboard.\u8232 \u8232 USE CASES FOR REGISTERED USER:\u8232 \'95 Register / Login / Logout\u8232 \'95 Post Question (with tags and rich-text body)\u8232 \'95 Edit / Delete own Question\u8232 \'95 Post Answer to a Question\u8232 \'95 Accept Answer (question owner only)\u8232 \'95 Upvote / Downvote Question or Answer\u8232 \'95 Post Comment on Question or Answer\u8232 \'95 Write and Publish Article\u8232 \'95 Bookmark Question\u8232 \'95 View and Update Profile\u8232 \'95 Receive and Read Notifications\u8232 \'95 Search Questions by keyword or tag\u8232 \'95 Reset Password via Email\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
