\f1\fs24 \cf0 4.5 Security Design\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Bug Overflow implements multiple layers of security:\uc0\u8232 \u8232 1. JWT Authentication: Access tokens (15 min) and refresh tokens (7 days) are stored in HTTP-only, Secure, SameSite=Strict cookies to prevent XSS and CSRF attacks.\u8232 \u8232 2. Password Security: Bcrypt with salt rounds of 12 ensures passwords are irreversibly hashed before storage. Plain-text passwords are never stored or logged.\u8232 \u8232 3. Rate Limiting: express-rate-limit middleware restricts each IP to 100 requests per 15-minute window on all API endpoints, preventing brute-force and DDoS attacks.\u8232 \u8232 4. Input Validation: All API inputs are validated on the server side before processing. HTML content from the rich-text editor is sanitised using DOMPurify before rendering.\u8232 \u8232 5. CORS Policy: The Express server is configured with a strict CORS policy, only allowing requests from the registered frontend origin.\u8232 \u8232 6. Environment Variables: Sensitive configuration (MongoDB URI, JWT secret, email credentials) is stored in environment variables, never in source code.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
