\fs24 \cf0 6.3 User Documentation\
Getting Started \'96 Installation Guide\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f10\fs20 \cf0 Prerequisites: Node.js 18+, MongoDB Atlas account or local MongoDB 6+, Git\uc0\u8232 \u8232 Step 1 \'96 Clone the Repository:\u8232     git clone https://github.com/krazy527/Bug-Overflow.git\u8232     cd Bug-Overflow\u8232 \u8232 Step 2 \'96 Configure Server Environment:\u8232     cd server\u8232     cp .env.example .env\u8232     # Edit .env with your values:\u8232     # MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://...\u8232     # JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key\u8232     # CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:3000\u8232     # EMAIL_USER=your_email\u8232     # EMAIL_PASS=your_app_password\u8232 \u8232 Step 3 \'96 Install Server Dependencies:\u8232     npm install\u8232 \u8232 Step 4 \'96 Configure Client Environment:\u8232     cd ../client\u8232     echo 'REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000' > .env\u8232 \u8232 Step 5 \'96 Install Client Dependencies:\u8232     npm install\u8232 \u8232 Step 6 \'96 Start the Application:\u8232     # Terminal 1 (server):\u8232     cd server && node index.js\u8232 \u8232     # Terminal 2 (client):\u8232     cd client && npm start\u8232 \u8232 Step 7 \'96 Access the Application:\u8232     Open http://localhost:3000 in your browser\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf0 User Guide\
Registering an Account\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Click 'Sign Up' on the navigation bar. Enter your name, email address, and a strong password. Click 'Register'. You will be logged in automatically and redirected to the home page.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Posting a Question\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Click 'Ask Question' button on the home page or navigation bar. Enter a clear, descriptive title. Write your question body using the rich-text editor \'97 include code snippets, formatting, and relevant details. Add 1-5 relevant tags. Click 'Submit Question'.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Answering a Question\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Navigate to any question by clicking its title. Scroll to the 'Your Answer' section at the bottom. Write your answer in the rich-text editor. Click 'Post Your Answer'.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Voting on Content\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Click the upward arrow (
\f9 \uc0\u9650 
\f1 ) to upvote a question or answer you find helpful. Click the downward arrow (
\f9 \uc0\u9660 
\f1 ) to downvote unhelpful content. Your vote affects the author's reputation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Accepting an Answer\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 If you are the question author, you can accept the best answer by clicking the checkmark (
\f13 \uc0\u10003 
\f1 ) icon next to any answer. Accepting awards +15 reputation to the answerer.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Bookmarking Questions\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Click the bookmark icon on any question to save it to your personal bookmark list. View all bookmarks from 'Bookmarks' in the navigation menu.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Writing Articles\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Navigate to 'Articles' and click 'Write Article'. Use the full-featured editor to write your technical article. Add a title and publish when ready.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Checking Notifications\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The bell icon in the navigation bar shows your unread notification count. Click it to view all notifications about votes, answers, and comments on your content.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Viewing Your Profile\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Click your username or avatar to view your profile page showing your reputation, badges, questions, answers, and articles. Click 'Edit Profile' to update your bio and avatar.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
